D

• [Dam](/Dam) – A barrier constructed across a [watercourse](/Surface_water) to obstruct, direct, or control the flow of water. Dams are vital for flood control, water supply for [irrigation](/Irrigation), [human consumption](/Tap_water), [industrial use](/Industrial_water), [aquaculture](/Aquaculture), and maintaining [navigability](/Navigability).

• [Damp proofing](/Damp_proofing) – Materials and techniques used to prevent moisture ingress into buildings.

• [Damped vibration](/Damped_vibration) – Vibration that decreases in amplitude over time due to energy dissipation.

• [Dead load](/Structural_load) – The weight of the structure itself and any permanent fixtures attached to it.

• [Deep cement mixing](/Deep_cement_mixing) – A ground improvement technique involving the mechanical mixing of cement with soil.

• [Deep foundation](/Deep_foundation) – Foundations that transfer loads to deeper, more competent soil or rock strata.

• [Deflection](/Deflection_(engineering)) – The displacement or movement of a structural element from its original position under load.

• [Deformation (engineering)](/Deformation_(engineering)) – The change in shape or size of a component or structure under load.

• [Deformation (mechanics)](/Deformation_(mechanics)) – A change in the form or size of a body.

• [Density](/Density) – The mass of a substance per unit volume.

• [Deployable structure](/Deployable_structure) – Structures designed to be compacted for transport and then expanded into their operational configuration.

• [Doric order](/Doric_order) – One of the three classical [Greek architectural orders](/Classical_architecture), characterized by its simple, sturdy columns and plain capital.

• [Double tee](/Double_tee) – A concrete structural element consisting of two parallel stems connected by a thin slab.

• [Dragon beam](/Dragon_beam) – A diagonal beam in a [timber-framed roof](/Timber_framing) that supports a hip rafter.

• [Ductility](/Ductility) – The ability of a material to deform under tensile stress without fracturing.

• [Dumpy level](/Dumpy_level) – A surveying instrument used to establish or verify horizontal lines.

• [Dynamic load testing](/Dynamic_load_testing) – A method of testing the capacity of a foundation by applying rapid, transient loads.

• [Dynamics](/Dynamics_(mechanics)) – The branch of mechanics concerned with the motion of bodies under the action of forces.

