F

• [Facade engineering](/Facade_engineering) – The design, construction, and performance of building envelopes, often referred to as facades.

• [Falsework](/Falsework) – Temporary structures used to support formwork or the structure itself during construction.

• [Fascia](/Fascia_(architecture)) – A flat architectural element, typically found at the edge of a roof.

• [Feasibility study](/Feasibility_study) – An assessment of the practicality of a proposed project or system.

• [Fibre-reinforced plastic](/Fibre-reinforced_plastic) – A composite material made from a polymer matrix reinforced with fibers.

• [Finite element method](/Finite_element_method) – A numerical technique used to find approximate solutions to boundary value problems in [engineering](/Engineering) and physics.

• [Fire protection engineering](/Fire_protection_engineering) – The discipline concerned with preventing and mitigating fires.

• [First fix](/First_fix_and_second_fix) – The initial stage of installation for building components, such as framing and roughing in utilities.

• [Flange](/Flange) – A projecting rim or edge on a structure, used for strengthening or for attachment to another object.

• [Flashing](/Flashing_(weatherproofing)) – A weather-resistant material used at junctions in building envelopes to prevent water ingress.

• [Flexibility (engineering)](/Flexibility_(engineering)) – The inverse of stiffness; a measure of how much a structure or component deforms under load.

• [Flitch beam](/Flitch_beam) – A composite beam made of timber and steel plates.

• [Fluid](/Fluid) – A substance exhibiting continuous deformation under shear stress.

• [Fluid mechanics](/Fluid_mechanics) – The branch of physics that deals with the behavior of fluids.

• [Fluid physics](/Fluid_physics) – The study of the physical properties of fluids.

• [Fluid statics](/Fluid_statics) – The study of fluids at rest.

• [Force](/Force) – An interaction that, when unopposed, will change the motion of an object.

• [Force lines](/Force_lines) – Lines representing the direction and magnitude of forces.

• [Formwork](/Formwork) – Temporary molds or structures used to contain and shape [concrete](/Concrete) until it hardens.

• [Foundation](/Foundation_(engineering)) – The part of a structure that transmits loads to the ground.

• [Fracture toughness](/Fracture_toughness) – A measure of a material's resistance to fracture when a crack is present.

• [Framing](/Framing_(construction)) – The structural skeleton of a building, typically made of wood or metal.

• [Friction](/Friction) – A force resisting the relative motion of solid surfaces, fluid layers, and material elements.

• [Furring](/Furring) – Thin strips of wood or metal used to create a level surface or provide spacing.

