M

• [Mass balance](/Mass_balance) – The principle that in a steady state, the rate of accumulation of mass within a system is zero.

• [Mass density](/Mass_density) – The mass of a substance per unit volume.

• [Material properties](/Material_properties) – The intrinsic characteristics of a material that determine its behavior under various conditions.

• [Materials science](/Materials_science) – The interdisciplinary study of the properties and applications of materials.

• [Metal alloy](/Metal_alloy) – See [Alloy](/Alloy).

• [Metallic bond](/Metallic_bond) – The type of chemical bond that holds metal atoms together in a metallic lattice.

• [Middle-third rule](/Middle-third_rule) – A design criterion for retaining walls, ensuring that the resultant force falls within the middle third of the base to avoid tension.

• [Midhinge](/Midhinge) – A type of hinge used in structural analysis to represent a connection that allows rotation but no translation.

• [Modified compression field theory](/Modified_compression_field_theory) – A theory used to predict the behavior of reinforced concrete members subjected to shear forces.

• [Modulus of elasticity](/Modulus_of_elasticity) – A measure of a material's stiffness, also known as [Young's modulus](/Young%27s_modulus).

• [Moment redistribution](/Moment_redistribution) – The process of adjusting internal bending moments in a structure to achieve a more favorable distribution, often used in indeterminate structures.

• [Monocoque](/Monocoque) – A structural technique where a structure's shell carries most of the stress, as opposed to using a load-bearing frame.

• [Multidisciplinary design optimization](/Multidisciplinary_design_optimization) – An approach to design that integrates expertise from multiple engineering disciplines to achieve optimal solutions.

• [Multi-function structure](/Multi-function_structure) – A structure designed to serve multiple purposes.

