N

• [Non-hydraulic cement](/Cement) – [Cement](/Cement) that does not harden in water, typically used for applications where moisture is absent.

O

• [Offshore construction](/Offshore_construction) – The installation of structures and facilities in marine environments, primarily for resource extraction and energy production. It's often referred to as maritime engineering.

• [Open web steel joist](/Open_web_steel_joist) – Lightweight steel trusses used for supporting floors and roofs.

• [Oriented strand board](/Oriented_strand_board) – A wood structural panel composed of cross-aligned strands of wood.

• [Ortman key](/Ortman_key) – A type of mechanical fastener.

• [Overhang](/Overhang_(architecture)) – A portion of a building's roof or floor that extends beyond the wall below.

P

• [Panel building](/Panel_building) – A construction method using prefabricated wall panels.

• [Permissible stress design](/Permissible_stress_design) – An older design method where stresses in structural members are kept below a predetermined allowable stress.

• [Pile cap](/Pile_cap) – A structural member that connects and distributes loads from columns or walls to a group of piles.

• [Pile splice](/Pile_splice) – A connection used to join two pile segments end-to-end.

• [Plastic hinge](/Plastic_hinge) – A localized region in a structural member where plastic deformation occurs under overload.

• [Plasticity](/Plasticity_(physics)) – The ability of a material to undergo permanent deformation without fracturing.

• [Plate (structure)](/Plate_(structure)) – A flat structural element, typically used in thin shells or as stiffeners.

• [Ply (layer)](/Ply_(layer)) – A single layer within a laminated material.

• [Post (structural)](/Post_(structural)) – A vertical, load-bearing structural member, often used in timber framing.

• [Pre-engineered building](/Pre-engineered_building) – A building whose components are fabricated off-site and then assembled on-site.

• [Prestressed concrete](/Prestressed_concrete) – Concrete in which internal stresses are introduced to counteract the stresses caused by external loads, improving its tensile capacity.

• [Prestressed structure](/Prestressed_structure) – A structure that utilizes prestressed concrete or other materials.

• [Progressive collapse](/Progressive_collapse) – The failure of one structural element that triggers a cascading failure of other elements.

• [Pyroshock](/Pyroshock) – A transient mechanical shock generated by pyrotechnic devices.

