T

• [T-beam](/T-beam) – A structural element with a T-shaped cross-section, often used as a beam or in composite construction.

• [Tainter gate](/Tainter_gate) – A type of adjustable gate used in dams and spillways.

• [Technical standard](/Technical_standard) – A document that establishes specifications, procedures, or criteria for products, processes, or services.

• [Tensile force](/Tensile_force) – A pulling force acting along the axis of a flexible medium.

• [Tensile modulus](/Tensile_Modulus) – See [Young's modulus](/Young%27s_modulus).

• [Tensile strength](/Tensile_strength) – The maximum stress a material can withstand while being stretched or pulled before breaking.

• [Tensile structure](/Tensile_structure) – Structures that employ tension as their primary load-bearing mechanism, such as tensile membrane structures.

• [Tensile testing](/Tensile_testing) – A method used to determine a material's tensile strength and ductility.

• [Tension member](/Tension_member) – A structural element subjected to tensile forces.

• [Thin-shell structure](/Thin-shell_structure) – A structure made from a thin, curved material that derives its strength from its shape.

• [Tie (cavity wall)](/Tie_(cavity_wall)) – A metal or plastic connector used to tie the inner and outer leaves of a cavity wall together.

• [Timber framing](/Timber_framing) – A construction method using heavy timber posts and beams to create the structural frame of a building.

• [Topology optimization](/Topology_optimization) – A mathematical method that optimizes material layout within a given design space for a given set of loads and constraints.

• [Torque](/Torque) – A twisting force that tends to cause rotation.

• [Torsion](/Torsion_(mechanics)) – The twisting of an object due to an applied torque.

• [Torsional vibration](/Torsional_vibration) – Vibrations involving twisting or rotational motion.

• [Toughness](/Toughness) – The ability of a material to absorb energy and deform plastically before fracturing.

• [Transient load](/Structural_load) – A temporary load applied to a structure, such as an impact or blast.

• [Trimmer](/Trimmer_(construction)) – A beam or joist used to frame an opening in a floor or roof.

• [Tripod (foundation)](/Tripod_(foundation)) – A foundation system consisting of three legs supporting a central column.

• [Truss](/Truss) – A structural framework of interconnected members, typically forming triangles, used to span large distances.

• [Truss connector plate](/Truss_connector_plate) – Metal plates used to join members in a wooden truss.

• [Twin bridges](/Twin_bridges) – Two parallel bridges built side-by-side.

