U

• [Ultimate tensile strength](/Ultimate_tensile_strength) – The maximum tensile stress a material can withstand before fracturing.

• [Universal beam](/I-beam) – See [I-beam](/I-beam).

• [Universal column](/I-beam) – A type of structural steel section with an H-shaped cross-section, used as columns.

V

• [Valve](/Valve) – A device that regulates, directs, or controls the flow of a fluid.

• [Vibration](/Vibration) – An oscillatory motion of a body or system about an equilibrium point.

• [Voussoir](/Voussoir) – A wedge-shaped masonry unit used in the construction of arches and vaults.

W

• [W-beam](/I-beam) – See [I-beam](/I-beam).

• [Weld access hole](/Weld_access_hole) – A notch cut into a joint to allow for proper welding.

• [Windpost](/Windpost) – A vertical steel member used to support masonry walls against wind loads.

• [Wood preservation](/Wood_preservation) – Treatment of wood to protect it from decay and insect attack.

• [Woodworking joints](/Woodworking_joints) – Methods of joining pieces of wood together.

X

• [X-bracing](/X-bracing) – A type of bracing system where diagonal members form an 'X' shape, providing stability.

Y

• [Yield](/Yield_(engineering)) – The point at which a material begins to deform plastically under stress.

• [Young's modulus](/Young%27s_modulus) – A measure of a material's stiffness or resistance to elastic deformation under tensile or compressive stress. Also known as the modulus of elasticity.

Z

• [Zero Defects](/Zero_Defects) – A quality management principle aiming to eliminate errors and defects.

